items.description: Veg Toofani is a popular Indian vegetarian dish made with a mix of colorful vegetables like bell peppers, carrots, beans, and onions, cooked in a rich and creamy tomato-based gravy, seasoned with a blend of spices, herbs, and a hint of tanginess. The name "Toofani" means "stormy" or "spicy", indicating the dish's bold flavors and spicy kick.
